One of the gubernatorial aspirants on the platform of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) and Senator representing the Uyo Senatorial District, Bassey Albert Akpan has defected to the Young Progressive Party (YPP). The defection is not unconnected with last week’s ruling of the Federal High Court in Abuja which dismissed the suit challenging the conduct of ward congresses held to elect Adhoc delegates of the PDP. Akpan who had resigned his membership of PDP on July 15, 2023, moved to his new political party with his supporters The ceremony which was held in his hometown Ibiono Ibom Eastern ward one, and witnessed by his supporters and well-wishers, had the Senator and wife, Imaobong, pick membership card numbers; 3887 and 5006, respectively from their new political party. Welcoming the Senate Committee Chairman on Petroleum and others into the new party, the Chairman of the party, Mr Yeneime Andy said YPP has become the fastest growing party in the state with the senator’s entrance. In appreciation of his people and the party, Akpan, declared himself a vessel in the hand of God to bring positive changes to Akwa Ibom state. He said though some persons boast in their ‘financial war chests, they can never buy the conscience and rights of the people. “Today, a new Akwa Ibom births. Akwa Ibom for you and Akwa Ibom for me. Akwa Ibom where there will be justice for all”, he said. POLL He commended the leadership of the party for rejecting all financial inducements from those who were described as “dubious elements” to do wrong. He offered himself to God, the Akwa Ibom people, and the party to use him to change Akwa Ibom State. In his words “2023 will be about “character, competence and capacity. I will never let Akwa Ibom people down. “I and my teeming supporters are joining the party to help build and improve the foundation so that it can form the next government of Akwa Ibom State,” he said.